=head1 DESCRIPTION

Defines a field to query for your application's Amazon CloudWatch
Internet Monitor data. You create a data repository by running a query
of a specific type. Each C<QueryType> includes a specific set of fields
and datatypes to retrieve data for.

=head1 ATTRIBUTES


=head2 Name => Str

The name of a field to query your application's Amazon CloudWatch
Internet Monitor data for, such as C<availability_score>.


=head2 Type => Str

The data type for a query field, which must correspond to the field
you're defining for C<QueryField>. For example, if the query field name
is C<availability_score>, the data type is C<float>.



